post_text: Lay Elementary Families: Here is an update and challenge from Principal Broughton. Tag your child Learning@Home this week so they can be in the spotlight!
shared_text:
Jesse D. Lay Elementary
September 8 at 5:11 PM ¬∑

Thank you all for your patience and understanding for the first day of Learning@Home. Parents got started bright and early. I had several messages before I entered the building at 8:30. I have tried to contact and respond to each person. There were some issues as we are all learning how to teach virtually. If you have an issue or question after school hours please don‚Äôt hesitate to send me an email at
Keith.broughton@knox.kyschools.us, also it is extremely important to stay current on all assignments. You will have daily lessons from your homeroom teacher, but Special classes will only assign one Library and one PE lesson per week. As we continue with Learning@Home, please take pictures of your child completing their assignments and tag our school Facebook page and their grade level Facebook page. I would love to fill this newsfeed with pictures of our students.

post_text: The Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) program is a financial resource for families with students who lost access to free or reduced-price school meals due to COVID-19. P-EBT provides households an EBT card with funds to spend on food at home for students. The P-EBT benefit is a one-time benefit with eligible households to receive up to $313.50 per eligible student. Apply: https://benefind.ky.gov/
